name: Ah Mah Homemade Cake Vivo City

reviews.text:
Nice traditional sponge cake.
It’s not that sweet and it’s great.
Tried the double flavours.
The cheese is with two layers of cheddar cheese at the bottom.
On top is the sponge cake.
The original is very soft and not too sweet too.

incident took place on15 Jan during lunch time around 12.50 PM. the lady wearing white shirt, Chinese, plump, in her 40s or older, rolled her eyes on me after I told her my order. i was polite and ordered ‘one cheese’. what was this rude lady doing at that time, she was cutting a big piece of cake and turned her back and picked up the cake right above the oven after hearing my order. i don’t mind waiting but why did she has to rolled her eyes on the customer? the whole experience was awful and i will stop buying from this outlet.

We bought one pack of castellan cake on last Sat afternoon between 3 pm to 5 pm for Sun breakfast.

The taste of the cake is not fresh as before. It could be unsold cakes for a certain duration. However we proceed to take as it's not spoilt.

However,  today we take a few more pieces and realized the taste is not right. We conclude the castella cake could have been unsold for few days or other reasons that result it's taste being not good.

Thus, we truly hope the management could look into maintaining freshness of the cakes.

In terms of customer services, it's generally ok. The cashier attending to us is polite. However there is another female staff who ignored us and turned her head away even when we said thank you.

Had tried their cakes before. This time tried their kuehs. Despite getting them in the evening,they still taste fresh and soft, not too sweet. The Ang ku kueh is a must buy. Better than some famous brands.

The store young lady is very very rude . I think the store boss owes her few months of salary. The cake is so bad, Half of the cake was uncooked and with runny dough. Worst, it turn sour.
This Ah Mah cake should have closed for good .
